        "user_preferences table (Step 1 — already planned)",
        "Monitoring/alerting for preference-read-miss rate and table row count divergence"
      ]
    },
    "database_safety": {
      "has_migrations": true,
      "reversible": true,
      "data_preserving": false,
      "large_table_impact": true,
      "details": "Step 1 (ADD TABLE) is safe and non-blocking. Step 3 (backfill) performs a bulk INSERT that could generate significant write I/O and WAL volume on large user tables — should be batched with throttling. Step 6 (DROP COLUMN) is irreversible and must not proceed until all data is verified migrated. The critical data safety issue is the backfill overwrite race: without a staleness guard, the backfill can silently destroy user preferences that were updated during the migration window."
    },
