      "reason": "Step 4's rolling deployment means for several minutes (or longer), different application instances read preferences from different sources. Combined with a potentially incomplete backfill, this causes some users to see their preferences vanish intermittently depending on which instance serves them. Without a feature flag or read-fallback pattern, there is no safe way to execute Step 4. Need MJ to confirm whether a feature flag or fallback-read pattern is architecturally preferred.",
